Geyskes Savannah (Tafelberg). Open shrub and herbaceous savannah growing in patchy clearings 40' to 100' wide surrounded by low tropical forest. Primary vegetation of grasses and sedges with low shrubs to 2 m tall. Open areas of sandstone covered with a thin layer of flooded spaghnum moss 6-8 thick growing directly on rock. Most plants growing in wet flooded conditions, which are probably subject to severe drought conditions during the dry season.
